2. cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the impact of cyber-physical attacks on additive manufacturing, which falls under the purview of cs.CY.
3. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes an object verification system using algorithms, which involves software engineering principles.
4. cs.SD (Software Development): The paper discusses the development of an object verification system using side-channel emanations, which involves software development.
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper outlines use cases incorporating the proposed approach, which involves human-computer interaction.
